''''Rekichū''' (暦注) refers to annotations in a {{ill|calendar|ja|暦|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} that indicate the auspiciousness (吉凶) of times, {{ill|directions|ja|方位|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and other elements related to the fortune (運勢) of particular days.
== Overview ==
Most Rekichū are based on the principles of {{ill|Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|ja|陰陽五行説|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|lt=Ten Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Twelve Earthly Branches|1=Earthly Branches|lt=Twelve Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|干支|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}). Generally, calendars list scientific and astronomical details such as dates, {{ill|days of the week|ja|曜日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|solar terms|ja|二十四節気|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and {{ill|72 pentads|ja|七十二候|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in the top section. The middle section typically features {{ill|Jūni choku|ja|十二直|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, while the lower section contains items like {{ill|Sembi|ja|選日|1=Senjitsu|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|28 mansions|ja|二十八宿|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Nine Star Ki|ja|九星|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and {{ill|Rekichū Gedan|ja|暦注下段|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. 
{{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} often appears under the date and is also considered part of Rekichū.
The method used to determine the dates in Rekichū is called {{ill|Senpō|ja|撰日法|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
