== Overview ==
Most Rekichū are based on the principles of {{ill|Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|ja|陰陽五行説|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 陰陽五行思想}} and the [[:en:Heavenly Stems|Ten Heavenly Stems]] and [[:en:Earthly Branches|Twelve Earthly Branches]] ([[:en:Sexagenary cycle|Sexagenary cycle]]). Generally, calendars list scientific and astronomical details such as dates, {{ill|days of the week|ja|曜日|1=day of the week|2=ja|3=曜日|qq=|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/days of the week|13=User:Immanuelle/Day of the week|qq=|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q41825}}, [[:en:Solar term|solar terms]], and {{ill|72 pentads|ja|七十二候|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/72 pentads|qq=}} in the top section. The middle section typically features {{ill|Jūni choku|ja|十二直|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jūni choku|qq=|1=Twelve Directions|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11404810}}, while the lower section contains items like {{ill|Sembi|ja|選日|1=Senjitsu|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sembi|13=User:Immanuelle/Senjitsu|qq=}}, [[:en:Twenty-Eight Mansions|28 mansions]], {{ill|Nine Star Ki|ja|九星|1=Nine Stars|2=ja|3=九星|lt=Nine Stars|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nine Star Ki|qq=}}, and {{ill|Rekichū Gedan|ja|暦注下段|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rekichū Gedan|qq=}}. 
{{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} often appears under the date and is also considered part of Rekichū.
The method used to determine the dates in Rekichū is called {{ill|Senpō|ja|撰日法|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senpō|qq=}}.
